PRACTICAL TITLE:
Demonstration of Network Diagnostic Tools (ping, ipconfig, tracert, arp, netstat, whois)

1. AIM
To study and demonstrate the use of various network diagnostic tools in Windows for analyzing network connectivity and performance.

2. THEORY
Network diagnostic tools are used to troubleshoot and analyze network-related issues. These tools help in checking connectivity, viewing IP configuration, tracing routes, and monitoring active connections.
Ping: Tests connectivity between two devices.
Ipconfig: Displays IP configuration details.
Tracert: Shows the path taken by data packets.
ARP: Maps IP addresses to MAC addresses.
Netstat: Displays active connections and ports.
Whois: Provides domain registration details.

